# GitHub Issue Creation

## Prerequisites
- Verify git repo with GitHub remote.
- Check `gh` CLI is available.

## Steps

### 1. Get Description
Accept natural language description of the issue.

### 2. Determine Type
Infer: Bug, Feature, Enhancement, Documentation

### 3. Generate Content
- Title: concise, under 70 chars
- Body: structured template based on type (bug → steps to reproduce, feature → proposed solution)

### 4. Preview and Confirm
Show generated content. Let user edit, add labels, assign.

### 5. Create Issue
`gh issue create --title "..." --body "..." --label "..."`

### 6. Show Result
Display issue URL and number. Suggest creating a branch with `/my-ops:branch`.
